494
00:37:06,130 --> 00:37:10,930
- I requested it specifically. Do you understand?
- Why?

495
00:37:12,330 --> 00:37:13,605
Andrew Laeddis,

496
00:37:14,850 --> 00:37:20,449
was the maintenance man in the apartment
building where my wife and I lived.

497
00:37:20,450 --> 00:37:20,925
Okay.

498
00:37:23,250 --> 00:37:25,200
He was also a firebug.

499
00:37:27,850 --> 00:37:30,325
Andrew Laeddis lit the match,

500
00:37:32,970 --> 00:37:36,495
that caused the fire that killed my wife.

501
00:37:43,530 --> 00:37:44,355
Let 'em out!

502
00:37:47,650 --> 00:37:49,649
What happened to Laeddis?

503
00:37:49,650 --> 00:37:53,350
Got away with it.
Laeddis got away with it and disappeared.

504
00:37:53,970 --> 00:37:56,169
About a year ago, I opened up the
newspaper and there he is.

505
00:37:56,170 --> 00:37:58,249
He's an ugly looking son of a bitch.

506
00:37:58,250 --> 00:38:00,769
He had a new scar from his right temple
down to his left lip.

507
00:38:00,770 --> 00:38:04,049
Eyes different colors.
Not the type of face you forget.

508
00:38:04,050 --> 00:38:07,129
He'd burned down a schoolhouse. Killed 2 people.

509
00:38:07,130 --> 00:38:08,969
He said voices told him to do it.

510
00:38:08,970 --> 00:38:11,569
First he was sent to prison
and then he was transferred here.

511
00:38:11,570 --> 00:38:13,648
- Then what?
- Then, nothing.

512
00:38:13,649 --> 00:38:17,448
He vanished like he never existed.
No record whatsoever.

513
00:38:17,449 --> 00:38:20,003
I'm sure he's not in ward B
that leaves ward C.

514
00:38:20,004 --> 00:38:21,168
Or he could be dead.

515
00:38:21,169 --> 00:38:26,319
So could Rachel Solando for that matter.
Lot of places to hide a body here.

516
00:38:27,049 --> 00:38:30,574
Only one place
no one really knows.

517
00:38:40,849 --> 00:38:44,728
That patient, Bridget Kearne,
when she sent me for water,

518
00:38:44,729 --> 00:38:47,648
she said something to you back there, didn't she?

519
00:38:47,649 --> 00:38:47,974
No.

520
00:38:50,729 --> 00:38:51,904
Come on boss!

521
00:38:55,449 --> 00:38:56,624
She wrote it.

522
00:39:11,649 --> 00:39:12,124
Boss!

523
00:39:13,329 --> 00:39:16,888
We gotta get indoors. It's turning
into fucking Kansas out here...

524
00:39:16,889 --> 00:39:19,189
- All right.
- Now. Let's go!

525
00:39:21,649 --> 00:39:22,549
Watch out!

526
00:39:25,249 --> 00:39:25,799
Jesus!

527
00:39:28,249 --> 00:39:30,324
Come on! Let's go back!

528
00:39:47,169 --> 00:39:49,144
Jesus Christ!
Damn it!

529
00:39:59,769 --> 00:40:03,719
- Are you okay boss?
- Yes. That's all right.

530
00:40:09,249 --> 00:40:11,968
So... if Laeddis is here...

531
00:40:11,969 --> 00:40:14,619
What are you going to do boss?

532
00:40:16,249 --> 00:40:18,824
I'm not here to kill Leaddis.

533
00:40:26,049 --> 00:40:29,524
If it was my wife
I'd kill him twice.

534
00:40:39,049 --> 00:40:44,799
When we got through the gates of Dakau,
the SS guards surrendered.

535
00:40:51,649 --> 00:40:56,624
The commandante tried to kill himself
before we got there...

536
00:40:58,249 --> 00:40:59,774
but he botched it.

537
00:41:00,969 --> 00:41:03,044
Took him an hour to die.

538
00:41:07,449 --> 00:41:11,674
When I went outside,
I saw all the bodies on the ground.

539
00:41:15,449 --> 00:41:16,974
Too many to count.

540
00:41:42,849 --> 00:41:44,599
Too many to imagine.

541
00:41:47,249 --> 00:41:47,924
So yeah

542
00:41:50,849 --> 00:41:56,049
The guards surrendered, we took
their guns, we lined them up...

543
00:42:36,969 --> 00:42:38,494
It wasn't warfare,

544
00:42:40,849 --> 00:42:42,099
it was murder.

545
00:42:46,369 --> 00:42:48,244
Yeah I've had enough of killing.

546
00:42:51,049 --> 00:42:53,174
That's not why I'm here.

547
00:42:53,849 --> 00:42:55,999
So what is this all about?

548
00:42:58,049 --> 00:42:59,974
After Laeddis vanished,

549
00:43:00,969 --> 00:43:04,744
I started doing some checking
on Ashecliffe.

550
00:43:04,969 --> 00:43:09,848
A lot of people knew about this place, but no
one wants to talk...

551
00:43:09,849 --> 00:43:12,599
You know? It's like they're scared of something

552
00:43:13,569 --> 00:43:17,248
You know this place is funded by
a special grant

553
00:43:17,249 --> 00:43:20,328
from the House of
Unamerican Activities Committee.

554
00:43:20,329 --> 00:43:26,248
HUAC. And how exactly are we fighting
the Commies from an island in Boston Harbor?

555
00:43:26,249 --> 00:43:29,374
By conducting experiments on the mind.

556
00:43:30,049 --> 00:43:31,528
At least that's my guess.

557
00:43:31,529 --> 00:43:33,448
And you think thats going on in here?

558
00:43:33,449 --> 00:43:35,648
Like I said, no one would talk, right?

559
00:43:35,649 --> 00:43:38,368
Until I found someone
who used to be a patient here.

560
00:43:38,369 --> 00:43:40,168
Guy's name is George Noyce.

561
00:43:40,169 --> 00:43:42,594
Nice college kid.
Socialist.

562
00:43:42,729 --> 00:43:46,248
He gets offered some money for some
psych study. Guess what they were testing?

563
00:43:46,249 --> 00:43:49,448
- Drug tests.
- So he starts seeing dragons everywhere.

564
00:43:49,449 --> 00:43:53,248
Almost beats his proffesor to death
Ends up here in Ashecliffe.

565
00:43:53,249 --> 00:43:53,924
Ward C.

566
00:43:55,169 --> 00:43:58,448
They released him after 1 year, right?
What does he do?

567
00:43:58,449 --> 00:44:03,769
Two weeks on the mainland he walks into
a bar and stabs three men to death.

568
00:44:03,770 --> 00:44:06,769
His lawyer pleads insanity,
but Noyce...

569
00:44:06,770 --> 00:44:08,849
stands up in the courtroom and

570
00:44:08,850 --> 00:44:10,649
he begs the judge,
for the electric chair.

571
00:44:10,650 --> 00:44:13,449
Anywhere but not a
mental hospital.

572
00:44:13,450 --> 00:44:16,975
Judge gives him life in the Dedham prison.

573
00:44:17,050 --> 00:44:21,049
- And you found him?
- Yes, I found him.

574
00:44:21,050 --> 00:44:22,125
He's a mess

575
00:44:23,170 --> 00:44:26,849
But it is pretty clear from what he tells me,

576
00:44:26,850 --> 00:44:29,729
they're experimenting on people here.

577
00:44:29,730 --> 00:44:31,530
I don't know, boss.

578
00:44:32,250 --> 00:44:35,729
- How do you believe a crazy guy?
- That's the beauty of it.

579
00:44:35,730 --> 00:44:40,249
Crazy people are a perfect subject.
They talk, but nobody listens.

580
00:44:40,250 --> 00:44:41,850
I stood in Dakau.

581
00:44:41,970 --> 00:44:46,729
We saw what human beings are capable
of doing to each other, right?

582
00:44:46,730 --> 00:44:49,129
For Christ sake we fought a goddamn war

583
00:44:49,130 --> 00:44:51,489
to stop them,
and now find out it may be happening here?

584
00:44:51,490 --> 00:44:53,015
On our soil?
No.

585
00:44:55,250 --> 00:44:58,129
So what are you really here to do, Teddy?

586
00:44:58,130 --> 00:45:00,480
I'm gonna get the proof,

587
00:45:00,570 --> 00:45:04,649
I'm gonna go back, and blow
the lid off this place.

588
00:45:04,650 --> 00:45:05,525
That's it.

589
00:45:06,570 --> 00:45:07,820
Wait a minute.

590
00:45:09,050 --> 00:45:11,649
You started asking around about Ashecliffe.

591
00:45:11,650 --> 00:45:16,729
Waiting for a chance to get out here
then suddenly they need a US marshal?

592
00:45:16,730 --> 00:45:19,489
I got lucky. There was a patient escape,
it was the perfect excuse.

593
00:45:19,490 --> 00:45:22,449
No, no, no boss.
Luck doesn't work that way.

594
00:45:22,450 --> 00:45:26,969
The world doesn't work that way. They got an
electrified fence around a septic facility.

595
00:45:26,970 --> 00:45:29,970
Ward C is inside a Civil War fort?

596
00:45:30,450 --> 00:45:34,449
A chief of staff with ties to the OSS
Funding from HUAC?

597
00:45:34,450 --> 00:45:38,449
Jesus Christ! Everything about this place
stinks of "government ops".

598
00:45:38,450 --> 00:45:40,449
- What If they wanted you here?
- Bullshit.

599
00:45:40,450 --> 00:45:42,249
- You were asking questions.
- Bullshit.

600
00:45:42,250 --> 00:45:47,369
Bullshit? We came in for Rachel Solando? Where is
one shred of evidence that she even existed?

601
00:45:47,370 --> 00:45:49,729
There's no way they could of known I'd be
assigned to this case. No way...

602
00:45:49,730 --> 00:45:52,649
While you were looking into them,
they were looking into you.

603
00:45:52,650 --> 00:45:55,204
All they need to do
is fake an escape to get you here.

604
00:45:55,205 --> 00:45:59,780
And now they have you.
They have us both, here, now.

605
00:46:01,770 --> 00:46:03,820
Marshal, are you out here?

606
00:46:04,130 --> 00:46:06,969
This is deputy warden McPherson.

607
00:46:06,970 --> 00:46:07,820
Marshal!

608
00:46:08,130 --> 00:46:10,329
How about that? They found us huh.

609
00:46:10,330 --> 00:46:13,849
It's an island, boss. They're always gonna find us.

610
00:46:13,850 --> 00:46:16,300
I know you are in there...

611
00:46:16,730 --> 00:46:19,569
We're getting off of this Goddamned island.
You and me.

612
00:46:19,570 --> 00:46:20,320
Come on!

613
00:46:24,330 --> 00:46:25,805
- Come on!
- Go!

614
00:46:35,530 --> 00:46:39,169
Get dried off.
Dr. Cawley wants to talk to you. Now!

615
00:46:39,170 --> 00:46:44,645
And hurry up, this thing is turning
into a goddamn hurricane!

616
00:46:47,450 --> 00:46:49,729
I dropped those suits off to be cleaned.

617
00:46:49,730 --> 00:46:51,649
It should be ready by tomorrow.

618
00:46:51,650 --> 00:46:54,425
That is if we don't all wash away first.

619
00:46:54,450 --> 00:46:59,049
Speaking of which, I'm afraid your smokes were
pretty much done for.

620
00:46:59,050 --> 00:46:59,525
So...

621
00:47:01,970 --> 00:47:03,969
This is our only choice, huh?

622
00:47:03,970 --> 00:47:07,049
Got something really nice in prison already
if that don't work for you...

623
00:47:07,050 --> 00:47:10,625
Now that you mention it, these are just fine.

624
00:47:10,650 --> 00:47:13,689
That's why I must repeat my insistence
that all ward C patients

625
00:47:13,690 --> 00:47:15,849
be placed in manual restraints.

626
00:47:15,850 --> 00:47:19,649
If the facility floods, they'll drown.
You know that.

627
00:47:19,650 --> 00:47:21,689
- That would take a lot of flooding.
- We are on an island,

628
00:47:21,690 --> 00:47:23,449
in the middle of the ocean,
during a hurricane.

629
00:47:23,450 --> 00:47:25,889
A lot of flooding seems like a
distinct possibility.

630
00:47:25,890 --> 00:47:28,489
It's a gamble, Steven.
say the power fails

631
00:47:28,490 --> 00:47:29,649
There's a backup generator.

632
00:47:29,650 --> 00:47:33,375
And if that goes? The cell doors
will open.

633
00:47:33,650 --> 00:47:35,525
Where are they going to go?
Hmm?

634
00:47:36,170 --> 00:47:39,049
They can't just hop a ferry, scoot over
to the mainland and wreak havoc.

635
00:47:39,050 --> 00:47:43,649
You're quite right. They're far more likely
to wreak havoc right here on us.

636
00:47:43,650 --> 00:47:47,169
If they're manacled to the floor, they'll die.

637
00:47:47,170 --> 00:47:48,570
That's 24 human beings.

638
00:47:49,250 --> 00:47:51,049
You can't live with that, can you?

639
00:47:51,050 --> 00:47:52,849
Frankly, if it were up to me,

640
00:47:52,850 --> 00:47:56,249
I'd put all 42 in ward A and B in
manual restraints as well.

641
00:47:56,250 --> 00:47:58,000
Excuse me
Excuse me

642
00:47:58,250 --> 00:48:01,604
- Marshal.
- I'm sorry doctor, I just have one quick question.

643
00:48:01,605 --> 00:48:02,849
Yes, I will be with you in a moment.

644
00:48:02,850 --> 00:48:05,649
We spoke this morning
about Rachel Solando's note

645
00:48:05,650 --> 00:48:07,449
The law of 4, I loved that.

646
00:48:07,450 --> 00:48:11,569
You said you had no idea what
that second line could refer to. Correct?

647
00:48:11,570 --> 00:48:12,445
Who is 67?

648
00:48:13,730 --> 00:48:17,449
Yes, I'm afraid I still don't.
None of us do.

649
00:48:17,450 --> 00:48:19,350
Uh huh. Nothing comes to mind.

650
00:48:21,170 --> 00:48:21,870
Nothing?

651
00:48:26,170 --> 00:48:28,689
Because I believe I just heard
you say that there are

652
00:48:28,690 --> 00:48:30,640
24 patients in ward C.

653
00:48:31,210 --> 00:48:33,649
And 42 of patients, in wards A and B

654
00:48:33,650 --> 00:48:38,049
Which means there is a total of what?
66 patients here in this facility.

655
00:48:38,050 --> 00:48:39,800
That is correct, yes.

656
00:48:42,730 --> 00:48:45,449
Then it seems that
Rachel Solando was suggesting

657
00:48:45,450 --> 00:48:48,050
you have a 67th patient, doctor

658
00:48:50,170 --> 00:48:53,129
- But I'm afraid we don't.
- This Is ridiculous.

659
00:48:53,130 --> 00:48:56,649
- What are you doing here?
- We are doing our goddamn job.

660
00:48:56,650 --> 00:48:59,969
Didn't McPherson tell you the good news?

661
00:48:59,970 --> 00:49:02,329
No, what's the good news, doctor?

662
00:49:02,330 --> 00:49:04,230
Rachel has been found.

663
00:49:05,130 --> 00:49:06,080
She's here.

664
00:49:07,570 --> 00:49:08,820
Safe and sound.

665
00:49:20,050 --> 00:49:22,475
There is not a mark on her.

666
00:49:25,530 --> 00:49:27,130
Who are these men?

667
00:49:30,050 --> 00:49:32,049
Why are they in my house?

668
00:49:32,050 --> 00:49:34,050
Police officers, Rachel.

669
00:49:34,450 --> 00:49:36,925
They... have a few questions.

670
00:49:39,050 --> 00:49:39,650
Ma'am.

671
00:49:43,970 --> 00:49:47,169
There's been a sighting of a known
Communist

672
00:49:47,170 --> 00:49:51,095
subversive in this area
passing out literature

673
00:49:51,970 --> 00:49:52,445
Here?

674
00:49:55,250 --> 00:49:57,025
In this neighborhood?

675
00:49:57,130 --> 00:49:58,855
Yes, I'm afraid so.

676
00:50:00,050 --> 00:50:03,649
If you can tell us what you did
yesterday, where you were,

677
00:50:03,650 --> 00:50:06,450
it would really help us narrow our search.

678
00:50:06,970 --> 00:50:07,520
Yes...

679
00:50:10,730 --> 00:50:11,630
Well, I...umm

680
00:50:15,170 --> 00:50:18,845
I made breakfast for Jim
and the children,

681
00:50:19,250 --> 00:50:20,425
and then I...

682
00:50:22,650 --> 00:50:25,650
I packed Jim's lunch
and he left.

683
00:50:28,170 --> 00:50:31,545
Then I sent the children off to school.

684
00:50:35,049 --> 00:50:36,024
And then...

685
00:50:42,449 --> 00:50:46,149
I decided to take a long swim in the lake.

686
00:50:52,049 --> 00:50:52,799
I see...

687
00:50:56,969 --> 00:50:58,294
And after that?

688
00:51:06,049 --> 00:51:07,174
After that...

689
00:51:16,449 --> 00:51:17,974
I thought of you.

690
00:51:24,049 --> 00:51:25,528
I... I'm sorry, ma'am.

691
00:51:25,529 --> 00:51:28,754
I don't know what you're talking about.

692
00:51:30,849 --> 00:51:34,474
Don't you know how lonely I've been, Jim?

693
00:51:39,249 --> 00:51:40,499
You're gone...

694
00:51:44,369 --> 00:51:45,469
You're dead.

695
00:51:50,449 --> 00:51:53,049
I cry every night.

696
00:51:58,049 --> 00:52:00,574
How am I supposed to survive?

697
00:52:02,649 --> 00:52:03,049
God.

698
00:52:13,169 --> 00:52:15,844
Rachel... it will be all right.

699
00:52:19,249 --> 00:52:21,049
I'm so sorry, but...

700
00:52:22,569 --> 00:52:25,544
everything is gonna be all right? Okay?

701
00:52:27,249 --> 00:52:28,349
I buried you.

702
00:52:30,649 --> 00:52:35,448
I buried an empty casket. Your body
rained down lumps of flesh splashing

703
00:52:35,449 --> 00:52:36,849
into the sea eaten by sharks.

704
00:52:40,849 --> 00:52:44,474
My Jim is dead,
So who the fuck are you?

705
00:52:46,649 --> 00:52:48,524
Who the fuck are you?!

706
00:52:49,169 --> 00:52:51,394
Who are you?! Who are you?!

707
00:53:01,049 --> 00:53:02,768
I'm sorry about that.

708
00:53:02,769 --> 00:53:06,048
I didn't want to interrupt, I thought
she might tell you something, but...

709
00:53:06,049 --> 00:53:08,088
we found her down by the lighthouse,

710
00:53:08,089 --> 00:53:09,439
skipping stones.

711
00:53:10,849 --> 00:53:14,448
We have no idea how she got out there. I'm going
to ask you both to go down into basement.

712
00:53:14,449 --> 00:53:18,448
There's food, water, and cots.
It's the safest place to be

713
00:53:18,449 --> 00:53:20,499
when the hurricane hits.

714
00:53:23,969 --> 00:53:25,968
Are you all right?
You look pale.

715
00:53:25,969 --> 00:53:27,969
I'm fine, it's just uh...

716
00:53:29,049 --> 00:53:30,724
Boss, are you okay?

717
00:53:31,729 --> 00:53:34,048
It's just so Goddamn bright? Isn't it?

718
00:53:34,049 --> 00:53:38,528
Photo sensitivity, headaches sometimes?
Marshal are you having a migraine?

719
00:53:38,529 --> 00:53:39,579
I'll be alright.

720
00:53:47,449 --> 00:53:50,888
- What's wrong with him.
- Take these, marshal. You'll sleep a couple
of hours, wake up clear as a bell.

721
00:53:50,889 --> 00:53:53,248
He's having a migraine.
Imagine someone sawed open your head and

722
00:53:53,249 --> 00:53:55,288
filled it with razors then shook it
as hard as they could.

723
00:53:55,289 --> 00:53:56,768
Take the pills, marshal.

724
00:53:56,769 --> 00:54:01,294
- No... I don't want the pills.
- It'll stop the pain. Take the pills.

725
00:54:04,969 --> 00:54:07,044
He's going to need to lie down.

726
00:54:28,049 --> 00:54:29,749
Careful. All right.

727
00:54:31,169 --> 00:54:32,994
Gonna be okay. Relax.

728
00:54:39,649 --> 00:54:41,474
- Who is that?
- Him?

729
00:54:42,449 --> 00:54:44,049
That's the warden.

730
00:54:46,049 --> 00:54:48,874
Don't you worry about him, alright?

731
00:54:54,329 --> 00:54:56,804
Looks like an ex-military prick.

732
00:54:57,649 --> 00:55:01,224
You know what? I ain't gonna argue
with you on that one.

733
00:56:21,969 --> 00:56:24,144
You should have saved me.

734
00:56:26,169 --> 00:56:28,970
You should have saved all of us.

735
00:56:57,050 --> 00:56:58,100
Hey buddy. Hey.

736
00:57:01,330 --> 00:57:02,030
Laeddis.

737
00:57:03,250 --> 00:57:03,650
Yes.

738
00:57:15,850 --> 00:57:16,750
Hi, buddy.

739
00:57:18,170 --> 00:57:20,220
No hard feelings, right?

740
00:57:26,450 --> 00:57:27,925
No hard feelings.

741
00:57:41,050 --> 00:57:43,325
Little something for later.

