01:21:18,746 --> 01:21:21,348
- No, I ...
- And if I say I'm not crazy ...

1006
01:21:21,949 --> 01:21:24,632
well that hardly helps, does it?

1007
01:21:25,954 --> 01:21:29,157
That's the Kafkaesque genius of it.

1008
01:21:32,160 --> 01:21:33,362
People tell the world you're crazy

1009
01:21:34,163 --> 01:21:35,444
and all your protests to the contrary,

1010
01:21:35,964 --> 01:21:37,086
just confirms what they're saying.

1011
01:21:40,169 --> 01:21:42,171
I'm not following you.
I'm sorry.

1012
01:21:42,651 --> 01:21:43,772
Once you are declared insane,

1013
01:21:44,653 --> 01:21:47,296
then anything you do is called
a part of an insanity.

1014
01:21:47,296 --> 01:21:49,899
Your reasonable protests
or denial.

1015
01:21:50,980 --> 01:21:53,102
Valid fears,
paranoia.

1016
01:21:53,102 --> 01:21:55,184
Survival instincts.

1017
01:21:55,785 --> 01:21:56,786
Defense mechanisms.

1018
01:21:57,787 --> 01:22:00,069
You're smarter than you look marshal.
That's probably not a good thing.

1019
01:22:00,910 --> 01:22:02,592
Tell me something...

1020
01:22:02,792 --> 01:22:03,913
Yeah...

1021
01:22:05,795 --> 01:22:07,396
What happened to you?

1022
01:22:08,197 --> 01:22:10,800
I started asking about these large
shipments of sodium-anatol.

1023
01:22:11,681 --> 01:22:14,604
- An opium-based hallucinogen.
- Psychotropic drugs.

1024
01:22:16,125 --> 01:22:17,407
I asked about the surgeries, too.

1025
01:22:20,690 --> 01:22:22,292
Ever heard of trans-orbital lobotomy?

1026
01:22:24,214 --> 01:22:25,495
They zap the patient with electroshocks,

1027
01:22:26,616 --> 01:22:30,340
then go through the eye with an ice pick

1028
01:22:31,421 --> 01:22:33,023
and pull out some nerve fibers.

1029
01:22:36,026 --> 01:22:37,347
Makes the patients much more obedient.

1030
01:22:38,428 --> 01:22:40,150
Tractable.

1031
01:22:40,951 --> 01:22:41,952
It's barbaric.

1032
01:22:43,353 --> 01:22:44,434
Unconscionable.

1033
01:22:45,635 --> 01:22:50,040
Do you know how pain enters the
body marshal? Do you?

1034
01:22:50,961 --> 01:22:52,322
Depends on where you hurt.

1035
01:22:53,243 --> 01:22:54,525
No, it has nothing to do with the flesh.

1036
01:22:55,125 --> 01:22:56,446
The brain controls pain.

1037
01:22:57,848 --> 01:23:01,452
The brain controls fear, empathy,
sleep, hunger, anger... everything.

1038
01:23:04,254 --> 01:23:05,135
What If you could control it?

1039
01:23:06,337 --> 01:23:07,338
The brain?

1040
01:23:07,458 --> 01:23:08,979
Re-create a man,

1041
01:23:10,180 --> 01:23:11,462
so he doesn't feel pain.

1042
01:23:12,062 --> 01:23:14,064
Or love. Or sympathy.

1043
01:23:15,866 --> 01:23:19,750
A man who can't be interrogated
because he has no memories to confess.

1044
01:23:22,753 --> 01:23:24,275
You can never take away
all a man's memories.

1045
01:23:24,475 --> 01:23:25,756
Never.

1046
01:23:25,997 --> 01:23:29,280
Marshal, the North Koreans
used American POWs

1047
01:23:30,081 --> 01:23:32,483
during their brainwashing experiments.

1048
01:23:32,563 --> 01:23:35,006
They turned soldiers into traitors.
That's what they are doing here.

1049
01:23:35,086 --> 01:23:39,490
They're creating ghosts to go out in the world.
And do things sane men never do.

1050
01:23:39,570 --> 01:23:42,278
To have that kind of ability, that kind of knowledge.

1051
01:23:42,861 --> 01:23:43,382
That would take years.

1052
01:23:44,576 --> 01:23:47,899
Years of research,
hundreds of patients to experiment on.

1053
01:23:49,901 --> 01:23:53,024
50 years from now,
people will look back

1054
01:23:53,024 --> 01:23:55,587
and say, "Here. This place
is where it all began."

1055
01:23:56,508 --> 01:23:58,590
The Nazis used the Jews.
The Soviets

1056
01:23:58,630 --> 01:24:01,193
used prisoners in their own gulags
and we...

1057
01:24:01,913 --> 01:24:03,034
We tested patients,

1058
01:24:03,835 --> 01:24:04,916
on Shutter Island.

1059
01:24:06,198 --> 01:24:07,719
No, they won't ...
No

1060
01:24:12,404 --> 01:24:13,525
You do understand

1061
01:24:17,129 --> 01:24:19,131
That they can't let you leave?

1062
01:24:19,651 --> 01:24:20,652
I am a federal marshal ...

1063
01:24:21,413 --> 01:24:22,735
They can't stop me.

1064
01:24:24,136 --> 01:24:25,257
I was an esteemed psychiatrist,

1065
01:24:27,620 --> 01:24:29,622
from a respected family.

1066
01:24:30,623 --> 01:24:32,144
It didn't matter.

1067
01:24:35,067 --> 01:24:36,148
Let me ask you ...

1068
01:24:37,149 --> 01:24:38,070
any past traumas in your life?

1069
01:24:42,955 --> 01:24:44,076
Yes. Why? Why would that matter?

1070
01:24:44,837 --> 01:24:46,439
Because they can point to some
event in your past and say

1071
01:24:46,479 --> 01:24:48,841
it is the reason you lost your sanity......

1072
01:24:49,562 --> 01:24:51,164
So that when they commit you here

1073
01:24:51,764 --> 01:24:55,368
Your friends and colleagues will say,
"Of course he cracked."

1074
01:24:56,369 --> 01:24:58,891
"And who wouldn't have,
after what he'd been through."

1075
01:24:58,891 --> 01:25:01,254
That could be said of anyone

1076
01:25:01,374 --> 01:25:03,897
- anyone at all.
- The point is they're going to say it about you.

1077
01:25:07,580 --> 01:25:08,701
How's your head?

1078
01:25:09,783 --> 01:25:12,305
- My head?
- Any funny dreams lately?

1079
01:25:12,986 --> 01:25:16,990
Trouble sleeping? Headaches?

1080
01:25:18,471 --> 01:25:20,193
I am prone to migraines. Yes.

1081
01:25:20,233 --> 01:25:21,194
Jesus!

1082
01:25:24,117 --> 01:25:25,318
You haven't taken any pills, have you?

1083
01:25:26,199 --> 01:25:28,539
- I mean even aspirin?
- They hit the aspirin?

1084
01:25:28,539 --> 01:25:30,045
Jesus!

1085
01:25:30,323 --> 01:25:33,407
And you ate the food in the cafeteria and drank
coffee they gave you.

1086
01:25:33,887 --> 01:25:36,009
You tell me at least that
you've been smoking your own cigarettes.

1087
01:25:38,612 --> 01:25:41,415
No... no.

1088
01:25:42,816 --> 01:25:44,017
No. I haven't.

1089
01:25:44,618 --> 01:25:47,541
It takes 36 to 48 hours for
neuroleptic narcotics...

1090
01:25:48,022 --> 01:25:51,025
To reach sufficient levels in
the blood stream.

1091
01:25:51,065 --> 01:25:52,826
Pulse becomes first

1092
01:25:53,827 --> 01:25:55,830
First the fingertips and then
eventually the whole hand.

1093
01:25:57,832 --> 01:26:01,035
Seen any waking nightmares lately,
marshal?

1094
01:26:04,318 --> 01:26:06,040
Tell me what goes on in that lighthouse?

1095
01:26:07,762 --> 01:26:08,843
Tell me.

1096
01:26:10,044 --> 01:26:11,926
Brain surgery.

1097
01:26:12,647 --> 01:26:16,370
"Let's open the skull and see
what happens if we pull on this" kind.

1098
01:26:16,931 --> 01:26:19,173
"We learned it from the Nazi's" kind.

1099
01:26:21,856 --> 01:26:23,578
It's where they create the ghosts.

1100
01:26:25,179 --> 01:26:27,061
Who knows about this?

1101
01:26:27,662 --> 01:26:29,384
On the island I mean. Who?

1102
01:26:31,746 --> 01:26:33,067
Everyone.

1103
01:26:33,188 --> 01:26:36,471
Oh come on. The nurses? The orderlies?

1104
01:26:37,472 --> 01:26:39,874
- They couldn't possibly know...
- Everyone.

1105
01:26:58,093 --> 01:27:00,215
You can't stay here.

1106
01:27:00,696 --> 01:27:04,019
They think I'm dead, that I drowned. I'm afraid
if they come looking for you, they might find me.

1107
01:27:05,020 --> 01:27:06,381
I'm sorry, but you have to go.

1108
01:27:13,509 --> 01:27:14,990
I'm gonna come back for you.

1109
01:27:15,231 --> 01:27:18,113
I won't be here. I move during the day.
new places every night.

1110
01:27:18,153 --> 01:27:20,436
But I could come get you
off of this island.

1111
01:27:20,436 --> 01:27:22,518
Haven't you heard a word I've said?

1112
01:27:23,119 --> 01:27:26,322
The only way off the island
is the ferry and they control it.

1113
01:27:26,922 --> 01:27:28,524
You'll never leave here.

1114
01:27:38,133 --> 01:27:39,454
I had a friend.

1115
01:27:39,935 --> 01:27:42,257
I was with him yesterday,
but we got separated.

1116
01:27:43,018 --> 01:27:44,539
Have you seen him?

1117
01:27:45,821 --> 01:27:47,342
Marshal...

1118
01:27:48,744 --> 01:27:50,465
You have no friends.

1119
01:28:21,898 --> 01:28:23,980
There you are.

1120
01:28:25,862 --> 01:28:28,184
We've been wondering when
you'd show up.

1121
01:28:30,066 --> 01:28:31,387
Have a seat.

1122
01:28:31,988 --> 01:28:33,189
Come on.

1123
01:28:43,720 --> 01:28:46,002
Taking a leisurely stroll? Were we?

1124
01:28:47,203 --> 01:28:48,605
I was just...

1125
01:28:49,326 --> 01:28:50,607
just looking around.

1126
01:28:53,209 --> 01:28:55,212
Did you enjoy
God's latest gift?

1127
01:28:56,813 --> 01:28:58,815
- What?
- God's gift.

1128
01:29:00,337 --> 01:29:01,818
The violence.

1129
01:29:06,503 --> 01:29:09,826
When I came downstairs in my home
and I saw that tree in my living room,

1130
01:29:10,827 --> 01:29:12,830
it reached down for me like a divine hand.

1131
01:29:14,431 --> 01:29:16,113
God loves violence.

1132
01:29:19,116 --> 01:29:21,719
- I hadn't noticed.
- Sure you have.

1133
01:29:22,359 --> 01:29:24,041
Why else would there be so much of it?

1134
01:29:24,842 --> 01:29:26,243
It's in us.

1135
01:29:26,443 --> 01:29:27,645
It's what we are.

1136
01:29:29,366 --> 01:29:32,570
We wage war, we burn sacrifices,
we pillage and plunder

1137
01:29:32,650 --> 01:29:34,211
and tear at the flesh
of our brothers

1138
01:29:34,251 --> 01:29:38,055
and why? Because God gave us violence
to wage in his honor.

1139
01:29:41,259 --> 01:29:43,421
I thought God gave us moral order.

1140
01:29:43,461 --> 01:29:46,063
There is no moral order
as pure as this storm.

1141
01:29:46,944 --> 01:29:48,946
There's no moral order at all.

1142
01:29:49,387 --> 01:29:52,870
There's just this:
can my violence conquer yours?

1143
01:29:58,276 --> 01:30:00,078
- I'm not violent.
- Yes you are.

1144
01:30:01,679 --> 01:30:03,481
You're as violent as they come.

1145
01:30:04,562 --> 01:30:07,285
I know this because I'm as violent as they come.

1146
01:30:08,406 --> 01:30:10,168
With the constraints of society,
we are lifted and

1147
01:30:10,488 --> 01:30:15,293
If I was all that stood between you and a meal, you
would crack my skull with a rock and eat my meaty parts.

1148
01:30:18,016 --> 01:30:19,498
Wouldn't you?

1149
01:30:22,180 --> 01:30:25,824
Cawley thinks you're harmless, that you can be
controlled, but I know different.

1150
01:30:26,985 --> 01:30:30,909
- You don't know me.
- Oh but I do. Oh I know you.

1151
01:30:31,910 --> 01:30:33,992
We've known each other for centuries.

1152
01:30:43,522 --> 01:30:46,125
If I was to sink my teeth into your eye
right now,

1153
01:30:46,165 --> 01:30:49,328
would you be able to stop me before I blinded you?

1154
01:30:53,332 --> 01:30:54,854
Give it a try.

1155
01:30:56,335 --> 01:31:00,339
That's the spirit.

1156
01:31:43,583 --> 01:31:45,065
Where have you been?

1157
01:31:46,186 --> 01:31:48,268
Wandering, just looking at your island.

1158
01:31:48,388 --> 01:31:52,512
Oh I forgot. You're leaving.
Now that Rachel has been found.

1159
01:31:52,993 --> 01:31:54,394
Sure. Yeah.

1160
01:31:56,597 --> 01:31:57,798
Big meeting?

1161
01:31:58,398 --> 01:32:00,801
Oh, yes ...

1162
01:32:00,881 --> 01:32:03,404
Apparently there was an unidentified man
in ward C yesterday

1163
01:32:03,444 --> 01:32:06,807
He subdued a highly dangerous patient.
Quite handily.

1164
01:32:08,008 --> 01:32:09,009
Is that so?

1165
01:32:09,129 --> 01:32:13,534
It seems he had a long conversation with a
paranoid schizophrenic, George Noyce.

1166
01:32:16,537 --> 01:32:19,300
This Noyce,
you said his name was,

1167
01:32:20,221 --> 01:32:23,264
- he's delusional?
- Oh extremely. He can be quite upsetting.

1168
01:32:23,304 --> 01:32:26,307
In fact, two weeks ago, a patient
got so wound up

1169
01:32:26,347 --> 01:32:30,111
by one of Noyce's stories
that he beat him up.

1170
01:32:30,431 --> 01:32:31,953
Cigarette?

1171
01:32:33,314 --> 01:32:35,036
Oh. No, thanks.
I quit.

1172
01:32:36,637 --> 01:32:38,639
So, you're taking the ferry?

1173
01:32:39,240 --> 01:32:40,561
Oh yes. Absolutely. I uh...

1174
01:32:41,242 --> 01:32:42,964
I think we've gotten
all we came here for so.

1175
01:32:43,845 --> 01:32:44,966
"We" marshal?

1176
01:32:47,128 --> 01:32:48,770
Speaking of which. Have you

1177
01:32:49,250 --> 01:32:51,573
- seen him, Doctor?
- Who?

1178
01:32:52,454 --> 01:32:53,975
My partner, Chuck.

1179
01:32:56,658 --> 01:32:58,580
You don't have a partner, Marshal.
You came here alone.

1180
01:33:01,062 --> 01:33:03,545
You know, I've built something valuable here.

1181
01:33:03,585 --> 01:33:06,948
And valuable things have a way of
being misunderstood in their own time.

1182
01:33:07,068 --> 01:33:08,950
Everyone wants a quick fix,
they always have.

1183
01:33:09,071 --> 01:33:12,474
I'm trying to do something that people,
yourself included, don't understand.

1184
01:33:12,594 --> 01:33:14,957
And I'm not going to give up
without a fight.

1185
01:33:16,358 --> 01:33:18,800
I can see that...

1186
01:33:22,484 --> 01:33:24,286
So tell me again
about your partner.

1187
01:33:26,168 --> 01:33:28,010
What partner?

1188
01:34:30,435 --> 01:34:32,076
Marshal...

1189
01:34:33,358 --> 01:34:34,759
Going somewhere?

1190
01:34:35,239 --> 01:34:38,763
No. Just heading out
to the ferry. So...

1191
01:34:40,365 --> 01:34:41,966
I'm afraid it's the other way.

1192
01:34:44,889 --> 01:34:46,691
If you wait a moment,

1193
01:34:47,252 --> 01:34:50,095
I'll find someone who can take you
to the dock.

1194
01:34:53,778 --> 01:34:56,221
What is this, doctor?

1195
01:34:56,261 --> 01:34:58,703
It's just a sedative.

1196
01:34:58,783 --> 01:35:01,306
- It's for precaution.
- Precaution?

1197
01:35:03,708 --> 01:35:07,793
What are you going to do?
Kill me? Marshal.

1198
01:35:08,313 --> 01:35:09,595
You think you deserve it?

1199
01:35:10,075 --> 01:35:12,798
For what?
For provoking you?

1200
01:35:13,318 --> 01:35:15,801
and, forgive me,
what doesn't provoke you?

1201
01:35:16,201 --> 01:35:17,322
Remarks...

1202
01:35:17,723 --> 01:35:19,084
- Words...
- Nazis!

1203
01:35:19,925 --> 01:35:21,407
Well that, too.

1204
01:35:21,927 --> 01:35:23,609
And of course, memories, dreams...

1205
01:35:24,810 --> 01:35:28,734
Did you know that the word "trauma" comes
from the Greek for "wound"?

1206
01:35:29,215 --> 01:35:33,299
And what is the German word for "dream"
"Traumen".

1207
01:35:33,339 --> 01:35:34,420
Traumen.

1208
01:35:35,741 --> 01:35:38,424
Wounds can create monsters.

1209
01:35:38,744 --> 01:35:41,227
And you ...
you are wounded, marshal.

1210
01:35:42,228 --> 01:35:45,031
Wouldn't you agree,
when you see a monster

1211
01:35:45,831 --> 01:35:47,233
you must stop it?

1212
01:35:50,236 --> 01:35:52,238
- I agree.
- Yes...

1213
01:36:37,004 --> 01:36:38,685
What are you doing, baby?

1214
01:36:43,811 --> 01:36:45,372
You've got to get to the ferry.

1215
01:36:46,013 --> 01:36:48,095
No. No.
No.

1216
01:36:52,099 --> 01:36:55,903
If the world thinks that Chuck is dead,
then he is perfect for their experiments.

1217
01:36:56,504 --> 01:36:58,986
There's only one place they'd take him.

1218
01:37:01,509 --> 01:37:03,911
You go there and you'll die.

1219
01:37:03,991 --> 01:37:07,835
He's my partner. If they are hurting him, if they are
holding him against his will, I've got to bring him out.

1220
01:37:08,196 --> 01:37:10,198
I can't lose anyone else.

1221
01:37:10,838 --> 01:37:14,842
Don't go, Teddy.
Please don't do this. Don't go.

1222
01:37:17,725 --> 01:37:19,607
I'm sorry, honey.

1223
01:37:21,329 --> 01:37:23,932
I love this thing because
you gave it to me

1224
01:37:26,614 --> 01:37:28,536
But the truth is ...

1225
01:37:28,616 --> 01:37:31,539
it's one fucking ugly tie.

1226
01:38:10,379 --> 01:38:11,500
No!

1227
01:39:30,060 --> 01:39:31,862
Don't move!
Stay where you are!

1228
01:39:33,464 --> 01:39:35,065
Are you going to kill me?

1229
01:39:35,466 --> 01:39:39,390
No.
I'm not gonna kill you.

1230
01:41:27,099 --> 01:41:29,861
Why are you all wet, baby?

1231
01:41:30,983 --> 01:41:33,385
- What did you say?
- You know exactly what I said.

1232
01:41:46,318 --> 01:41:48,681
The rifle's empty by the way.

1233
01:41:54,126 --> 01:41:55,928
Have a seat.

1234
01:42:02,415 --> 01:42:05,498
For god's sake dry off
you're going to catch a cold.

1235
01:42:06,619 --> 01:42:07,620
Alright.

1236
01:42:10,223 --> 01:42:12,905
How badly did you hurt the guard?

1237
01:42:15,508 --> 01:42:17,630
I don't know what
you're talking about.

1238
01:42:20,353 --> 01:42:21,915
Yes. He's here.

1239
01:42:22,435 --> 01:42:25,358
Have Dr.Sheehan take a good look
at your man before you send him up.

1240
01:42:27,040 --> 01:42:28,842
So, Dr. Shehan...

1241
01:42:29,442 --> 01:42:30,643
He came on the ferry
this morining.

1242
01:42:31,645 --> 01:42:32,646
Not exactly.

1243
01:42:34,367 --> 01:42:36,850
You blew up my car.
I really loved that car.

1244
01:42:38,171 --> 01:42:39,853
Sorry to hear about that.

1245
01:42:43,176 --> 01:42:44,738
Tremors are getting pretty bad.

1246
01:42:46,179 --> 01:42:47,260
How are the hallucinations?

1247
01:42:48,261 --> 01:42:49,663
Get out of here, Teddy.

1248
01:42:50,864 --> 01:42:52,666
This place is gonna be the end of you.

1249
01:42:55,589 --> 01:42:58,272
- Not bad.
- They'll get worse.

1250
01:42:58,752 --> 01:42:59,793
I know.

1251
01:43:00,674 --> 01:43:02,076
Dr. Solando...

1252
01:43:02,997 --> 01:43:05,359
She told me about neuroleptics.

1253
01:43:05,479 --> 01:43:08,682
Did she now?
And when was this?

